parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic seat belt can cause the driver or passenger to be unrestrained, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt is stuck in the forward position
the shoulder belt will not retract
the belt does not reach around the driver or passenger
the belt operates slowly
the retractor sticks halfway
the belt does not hold the driver or passenger in place during an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water leaks into the passenger compartment can cause damage to electrical components, rust, and corrosion, leading to safety hazards and costly repairs.
symptoms: Water accumulation on the front passenger floor board
water accumulation on the driver-side floor of the trunk
water spots or stains on the interior carpets and upholstery.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Broken door handles can make it difficult or impossible to enter or exit the vehicle, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Door handles break off from the vehicle
difficulty opening or closing doors
doors become stuck or jammed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the metal bracket attached to the body of the vehicle, above the fuel tank, can cause a hole to wear into the top of the tank, leading to fuel leakage, which can result in a fire or explosion.
symptoms: Fuel leakage from the top of the tank
fuel smell or odor
decreased fuel efficiency
potential fire or explosion.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sluggish acceleration can increase the stopping distance, making it difficult to merge or change lanes, which can lead to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: Vehicle hesitates or lags when accelerating
slow response to throttle input
difficulty merging or changing lanes
decreased engine performance.
